The paper discusses the training of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) using Optimistic Mirror Decent (OMD) and Optimistic Adam, which are optimization algorithms commonly used in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of GANs and optimization. The paper also discusses the application of OMD to a bioinformatics problem, which suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
